{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778979370047,"sessionID":"ses_1cc994489ffeFlBi4C0jxCUInA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_chAVl8CsyY7CpZi3Blbgazz9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://enzyme.expasy.org/EC/1.14.14.24","format":"markdown","timeout":60},"output":"         ENZYME - 1.14.14.24 vitamin D 25-hydroxylase\n\n![Expasy logo](/images/expasy_logos/Expasy_logo_base_addon.svg)\n\n#### [ENZYME](https://enzyme.expasy.org)\n\n-   ![home](/images/icons/home.svg) [Home](/index.html)\n-   ![tool](/images/icons/tool.svg) [Browse](/cgi-bin/enzyme/enzyme-search-cl?1)\n    -   [by classes](/cgi-bin/enzyme/enzyme-search-cl?1)\n    -   [by subclasses](/cgi-bin/enzyme/enzyme-search-cl?2)\n    -   [by subsubclasses](/cgi-bin/enzyme/enzyme-search-cl?3)\n-   ![browse](/images/icons/browse.svg) [Search](/enzyme-search-ec.html)\n    -   [by EC number](/enzyme-search-ec.html)\n    -   [by name](/enzyme-byname.html)\n    -   [by chemical compound](/enzyme-bycompound.html)\n    -   [by comment](/enzyme-bycomment.html)\n-   ![documents](/images/icons/documents.svg) [Documentation](https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/enzyme/)\n    -   [User Manual](https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/enzyme/enzuser.txt)\n    -   [Access to ENZYME](https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/enzyme/enzyme.get)\n-   ![download](/images/icons/download.svg) [Downloads](https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/enzyme/)\n-   ![contact](/images/icons/contact.svg) [Contact](/contact)\n\n# ENZYME entry: EC 1.14.14.24\n\n[PURL](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persistent_uniform_resource_locator): [https://purl.expasy.org/enzyme/EC/1.14.14.24](https://purl.expasy.org/enzyme/EC/1.14.14.24)\n\nAccepted Name\n\n**vitamin D 25-hydroxylase**\n\nAlternative Name(s)\n\n**CYP2R1**\n\n**vitamin D2 25-hydroxylase**\n\n**vitamin D3 25-hydroxylase**\n\nReaction catalysed\n\ncalciol + reduced \\[NADPH--hemoprotein reductase\\] + O2 = calcidiol + oxidized \\[NADPH--hemoprotein reductase\\] + H2O + H(+)\n\nComment(s)\n\n-   A microsomal enzyme isolated from human and mouse liver that bioactivates vitamin D3.\n-   While multiple isoforms (CYP27A1, CYP2J2/3, CYP3A4, CYP2D25 and CYP2C11) are able to catalyze the reaction in vitro, only CYP2R1 is thought to catalyze the reaction in humans in vivo.\n-   The direct electron donor to the enzyme is EC [1.6.2.4](/EC/1.6.2.4).\n-   Formerly EC 1.14.13.159.\n\nCross-references\n\nRhea expert-curated reactions\n\n[1.14.14.24](https://www.rhea-db.org/rhea?query=ec%3A1.14.14.24)\n\nExplorEnz\n\n[1.14.14.24](http://www.enzyme-database.org/query.php?ec=1.14.14.24)\n\nIUBMB Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.14.14.24](https://www.qmul.ac.uk/sbcs/iubmb/enzyme/EC1/14/14/24.html)\n\nUniProtKB/Swiss-Prot\n\n[O46658](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/O46658), CP2DP\\_PIG\n\n[Q6VVX0](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q6VVX0), CP2R1\\_HUMAN\n\n[Q6VVW9](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q6VVW9), CP2R1\\_MOUSE\n\nBRENDA\n\n[1.14.14.24](http://www.brenda-enzymes.org/enzyme.php?ecno=1.14.14.24)\n\nMetaCyc\n\n[1.14.14.24](https://biocyc.org/META/NEW-IMAGE?type=EC-NUMBER&object=EC-1.14.14.24)\n\nKEGG Ligand Database for Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.14.14.24](http://www.genome.ad.jp/dbget-bin/www_bget?ec:1.14.14.24)\n\nEC2PDB\n\n[1.14.14.24](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/thornton-srv/databases/cgi-bin/enzymes/GetPage.pl?ec_number=1.14.14.24)\n\nMEDLINE\n\n[Find literature relating to 1.14.14.24](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=PureSearch&db=PubMed&details_term=1.14.14.24[EC/RN%20Number])\n\n  \n[View entry in original ENZYME format](/cgi-bin/enzyme/get-enzyme-entry?1.14.14.24)  \n[View entry in raw text format (no links)](/EC/1.14.14.24.txt)  \n\n[All UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries referenced in this entry](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.14.14.24\\)%20AND%20\\(reviewed:true\\)), with possibility to download in different formats, align etc.\n\nAll [ENZYME](/EC/1.14.14.-) / [UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.14.14.