ase activity terms.\n+- `EC:1.17.3.2` covers both hypoxanthine oxidase and xanthine oxidase reactions, so `broadMatch` is the appropriate mapping qualifier for the corresponding GO terms rather than `exactMatch`.\n+- The accepted EC name for `EC:1.14.14.24` is `vitamin D 25-hydroxylase`, so the GO label was updated to match while retaining the previous wording as a synonym.\n+- `RHEA:68012` was added as both exact xref and definition provenance for `GO:0070675` per the request.\n+\n+Validation and workflow:\n+\n+- Read issue context from `__issue_context__.json`.\n+- Used the GO catalytic activity/reaction guidance and checked existing term precedent before editing.\n+- Performed pre-validation with `make travis_build` before changes.\n+- Edited terms via `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` rather than modifying the large edit file directly.\n+- Performed post-change validation with `make travis_build`; validation passed.\n+\n+Checklist:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue analyzed and scope clear\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: ontology validated before edits\n+- [x] RESEARCH: not needed beyond source database/term verification for this xref update\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: relevant GO terms consulted\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: catalytic activity/reaction term precedent consulted\n+- [x] EDITS: used checkout/checkin workflow in `terms/`\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: no relationship changes required\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: reaction guidance consulted\n+- [x] METADATA: issue tracker metadata added to touched terms; no new terms created\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after changes\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: EC and RHEA identifiers checked against the issue request and existing ontology conventions\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: ontology edits committed locally\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n=========================